1
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:21,680
Sister Dolma

2
00:01:23,599 --> 00:01:24,319
Teach me how

3
00:01:28,079 --> 00:01:28,640
Sure

4
00:01:29,079 --> 00:01:29,560
Come here

5
00:01:37,159 --> 00:01:38,400
Put your foot on the outside

6
00:01:38,879 --> 00:01:39,319
That's it

7
00:01:41,359 --> 00:01:41,879
Step down

8
00:01:43,239 --> 00:01:43,680
That's right

9
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:46,200
Watch me

10
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,879
Hold your hands like this

11
00:01:49,439 --> 00:01:49,840
Yes

12
00:01:50,159 --> 00:01:50,680
Take this

13
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:02,879
Have a safe trip

14
00:02:03,560 --> 00:02:04,079
Don't worry

15
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:06,519
All right

16
00:02:07,439 --> 00:02:08,280
There's no need to see me off

17
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:10,039
I'll be back in a few days

18
00:02:10,360 --> 00:02:11,199
Everyone, wait a moment

19
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:14,080
I made some milk tea

20
00:02:14,639 --> 00:02:15,759
I want everyone to try it

21
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:23,599
Delicious

22
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:25,039
Uncle Jimei

23
00:02:25,560 --> 00:02:27,960
This milk tea looks and tastes great

24
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:28,639
It's a new recipe

25
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:32,120
I used Himalayan Sacred Tea as the base

26
00:02:32,680 --> 00:02:35,039
Then added Rhodiola and Highland Yak Milk

27
00:02:35,599 --> 00:02:36,759
For aroma and looks

28
00:02:37,120 --> 00:02:39,240
I sprinkled some fresh peach blossoms from our village

29
00:02:40,199 --> 00:02:41,000
It's tasty

30
00:02:41,280 --> 00:02:42,599
Sister Nana, you try it too

31
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:52,039
Nana

32
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:03,599
Not bad

33
00:03:05,520 --> 00:03:06,120
Bro Jimei

34
00:03:06,240 --> 00:03:07,879
We must promote such great milk tea

35
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,319
Let's call it

36
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:10,759
Peach Blossom Milk Tea

37
00:03:11,960 --> 00:03:13,639
Can't we come up with a catchier name?

38
00:03:13,759 --> 00:03:14,439
Exactly

39
00:03:14,439 --> 00:03:15,919
We should pick a catchier name

40
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,280
Don't rush, everyone

41
00:03:17,439 --> 00:03:17,960
Head back

42
00:03:18,159 --> 00:03:18,759
Take your time thinking

43
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:20,919
All right

44
00:03:21,199 --> 00:03:21,759
I'm off

45
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:26,960
Goodbye

46
00:03:27,159 --> 00:03:27,639
Goodbye

47
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:32,639
Take care

48
00:03:38,800 --> 00:03:39,560
So nice

49
00:03:42,080 --> 00:03:42,400
Let's go

50
00:03:42,840 --> 00:03:43,280
Come on

51
00:03:48,879 --> 00:03:49,759
Let's unload, Uncle Liu

52
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,479
I'll help you

53
00:03:54,159 --> 00:03:54,960
Careful, careful

54
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,719
It's fine, it's fine

55
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,639
Here, put it down

56
00:03:57,639 --> 00:03:58,080
Give me a hand

57
00:04:00,520 --> 00:04:01,319
Uncle Liu

58
00:04:01,599 --> 00:04:02,680
So many vegetables today

59
00:04:02,759 --> 00:04:03,879
And they still have soil on them

60
00:04:03,960 --> 00:04:04,719
Of course

61
00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:06,319
These fruits and vegetables

62
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:07,919
I've been tending them for over twenty years

63
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:09,360
Every single one is as fresh as can be

64
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:10,960
Uncle Liu

65
00:04:11,319 --> 00:04:12,919
Then I want to eat them for 20 years

66
00:04:12,919 --> 00:04:14,199
Forty years, eighty years

67
00:04:14,840 --> 00:04:15,599
Wow

68
00:04:15,639 --> 00:04:16,199
All right

69
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,680
Then I'll grow them for another 80 years

70
00:04:20,240 --> 00:04:21,920
All right, I still have many deliveries to make

71
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:22,639
I'll get going

72
00:04:22,639 --> 00:04:23,720
Sit for a bit before you go, Uncle

73
00:04:24,439 --> 00:04:25,160
You young folks

74
00:04:25,480 --> 00:04:25,920
Have a good chat

75
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:27,720
I'm off, Zhaxi

76
00:04:28,079 --> 00:04:29,000
Cover that with the blanket for me

77
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:31,399
Here

78
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:33,399
I'm leaving

79
00:04:33,399 --> 00:04:33,959
Take it easy, Uncle

80
00:04:40,439 --> 00:04:41,240
Did you know?

81
00:04:41,879 --> 00:04:43,680
Uncle Liu's greenhouse is being torn down

82
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:46,000
Really?

83
00:04:46,959 --> 00:04:48,160
The village is building a road

84
00:04:48,160 --> 00:04:49,160
And it goes right through there

85
00:04:57,639 --> 00:04:58,000
Uncle.

86
00:04:58,519 --> 00:04:59,519
Try this tea.

87
00:04:59,519 --> 00:05:00,199
This tea is really good.

88
00:05:00,399 --> 00:05:01,079
Okay.

89
00:05:01,480 --> 00:05:02,319
Just a little, a little.

90
00:05:04,600 --> 00:05:05,040
Okay, okay.

91
00:05:05,759 --> 00:05:06,319
Thank you.

92
00:05:09,079 --> 00:05:09,560
Party Secretary.

93
00:05:09,839 --> 00:05:10,680
Let's get started.

94
00:05:12,879 --> 00:05:13,319
Let's begin.

95
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:18,120
Here's the situation.

96
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:20,360
The main road must be widened by 6 meters.

97
00:05:21,120 --> 00:05:21,800
Keep it straight.

98
00:05:22,040 --> 00:05:23,800
This is the backbone of our whole scenic area.

99
00:05:24,639 --> 00:05:26,120
So in that case,

100
00:05:26,879 --> 00:05:28,120
Uncle Liu's greenhouses

101
00:05:29,319 --> 00:05:30,319
will need to be torn down.

102
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:38,079
Xiao Zhang.

103
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,920
I didn't quite catch what you said.

104
00:05:41,519 --> 00:05:43,319
You mean my greenhouses have to go too?

105
00:05:44,759 --> 00:05:45,959
But over on the west side of the village,

106
00:05:45,959 --> 00:05:47,279
we'll allocate you a new plot of land

107
00:05:47,600 --> 00:05:48,399
as compensation.

108
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,079
The west side of the village?

109
00:05:51,639 --> 00:05:52,879
Everyone knows that land.

110
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,079
That's uncultivated land.

111
00:05:54,199 --> 00:05:55,360
Nothing decent grows there.

112
00:05:57,000 --> 00:05:58,079
As for developing tourism,

113
00:05:58,319 --> 00:05:59,079
I'm not against it.

114
00:05:59,759 --> 00:06:00,920
But you can't take away my livelihood.

115
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:03,560
Uncle.

116
00:06:04,399 --> 00:06:05,839
This is for the whole village's development.

117
00:06:06,079 --> 00:06:07,040
Enough, enough, enough.

118
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:09,040
Spare me the lecture.

119
00:06:10,199 --> 00:06:11,240
Now you're preaching.

120
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:12,839
Over twenty years ago,

121
00:06:12,959 --> 00:06:14,360
I had just a bedroll on my back

122
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,879
when I came to Peach Blossom Village.

123
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,600
it was this land that took me in.

124
00:06:20,759 --> 00:06:21,600
For over twenty years,

125
00:06:22,040 --> 00:06:24,360
this land has never let me down.

126
00:06:24,519 --> 00:06:26,240
And I won't let it down now.

127
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,199
Right.

128
00:06:27,199 --> 00:06:28,480
We're having a meeting today, aren't we?

129
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:30,079
We can renegotiate the compensation.

130
00:06:30,079 --> 00:06:31,000
There's nothing to discuss.

131
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:32,680
Compensation, compensation.

132
00:06:32,680 --> 00:06:33,720
That's all you talk about.

133
00:06:34,839 --> 00:06:35,920
That little compensation of yours,

134
00:06:36,319 --> 00:06:38,160
can it make up for 20 years of hard work?

135
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:41,360
Can it make up for the land

136
00:06:41,480 --> 00:06:43,199
I worked with these hands for 20 years?

137
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,879
Listen here, Cadre Xiao Zhang.

138
00:06:46,240 --> 00:06:47,240
Have you ever farmed?

139
00:06:47,800 --> 00:06:49,720
Do you know how soil becomes cultivated?

140
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,240
It's hoed out one stroke at a time.

141
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:55,160
Do you know how this greenhouse was built?

142
00:06:55,519 --> 00:06:57,639
One bamboo pole at a time.

143
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,480
And you just want to tear it all down?

144
00:07:08,680 --> 00:07:09,279
Uncle Liu.

145
00:07:10,839 --> 00:07:11,560
Party Secretary Wangdui.

146
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:12,639
Please sit down.

147
00:07:13,279 --> 00:07:14,480
I know you have a bad back.

148
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:16,279
I just want to ask you one thing.

149
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,600
If your land was in the way,

150
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,519
would you tear it down or not?

151
00:07:31,279 --> 00:07:31,800
Forget it.

152
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,199
Party Secretary.

153
00:07:33,639 --> 00:07:35,639
My land is waiting for the chicken manure.

154
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:37,720
I'm heading off.

155
00:07:40,959 --> 00:07:43,480
Uncle Liu is really angry this time.

156
00:07:45,040 --> 00:07:45,600
Party Secretary.

157
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,680
This is going to be tough.

158
00:07:50,439 --> 00:07:51,639
I know his temper.

159
00:07:52,800 --> 00:07:53,680
It's not about the money.

160
00:07:55,199 --> 00:07:56,000
That land is his life.

161
00:08:14,839 --> 00:08:15,240
Party Secretary.

162
00:08:16,759 --> 00:08:17,399
You haven't left yet?

163
00:08:18,160 --> 00:08:19,079
I can't leave.

164
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:20,839
Uncle Liu's issue isn't resolved.

165
00:08:20,839 --> 00:08:21,639
I can't submit the proposal.

166
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:24,720
Party Secretary.

167
00:08:25,759 --> 00:08:27,240
What Uncle Liu said,

168
00:08:28,439 --> 00:08:29,759
if your house was blocking the road,

169
00:08:30,519 --> 00:08:31,319
would you move?

170
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:32,919
Honestly,

171
00:08:33,960 --> 00:08:34,840
I really can't answer that.

172
00:08:36,799 --> 00:08:38,039
I can't answer it either.

173
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,320
So what do we do?

174
00:08:41,399 --> 00:08:42,480
That greenhouse of his

175
00:08:43,039 --> 00:08:44,440
really is his lifeblood.

176
00:08:45,360 --> 00:08:46,360
But this road of ours

177
00:08:46,840 --> 00:08:48,159
is the lifeblood of the whole village.

178
00:08:49,679 --> 00:08:51,159
So we...

179
00:08:51,879 --> 00:08:53,960
So we need him to come around on his own.

180
00:08:56,159 --> 00:08:57,120
Will he come around?

181
00:08:58,039 --> 00:08:58,879
I don't know.

182
00:08:59,440 --> 00:09:00,759
But he's not an unreasonable man.

183
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:04,320
Right.

184
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:06,440
He's not an unreasonable man.

185
00:09:09,240 --> 00:09:09,559
Party Secretary.

186
00:09:10,559 --> 00:09:11,639
Let me help apply the medicinal liquor.

187
00:09:12,559 --> 00:09:13,919
Okay, okay, let's go.

188
00:09:33,480 --> 00:09:33,960
Uncle.

189
00:09:37,039 --> 00:09:37,600
Busy, I see.

190
00:09:38,360 --> 00:09:39,600
These vegetables are growing so well.

191
00:09:41,039 --> 00:09:41,559
Party Secretary, you're here.

192
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,360
Uncle.

193
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:45,440
Please calm down.

194
00:09:45,759 --> 00:09:46,399
Don't take it to heart.

195
00:09:48,399 --> 00:09:49,000
Come on, step aside.

196
00:09:56,039 --> 00:09:57,679
You're tearing down his lifeblood.

197
00:09:58,320 --> 00:09:59,600
And now you come running over here

198
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:00,799
telling him not to be angry?

199
00:10:01,759 --> 00:10:02,480
Cadre Zhang.

200
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:04,399
You're not welcome here.

201
00:10:04,519 --> 00:10:05,120
Please leave.

202
00:10:07,639 --> 00:10:08,120
Uncle.

203
00:10:08,840 --> 00:10:10,159
The whole village is watching.

204
00:10:10,759 --> 00:10:11,519
If you'll just give the word,

205
00:10:12,320 --> 00:10:13,159
that plot at the west end of the village,

206
00:10:13,559 --> 00:10:14,840
I'll have people sift soil and fertilize.

207
00:10:15,440 --> 00:10:17,039
I'll turn it into good cultivated soil.

208
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,559
It won't delay your vegetable planting.

209
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:19,960
We can talk about the rest later.

210
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:20,600
All right?

211
00:10:20,879 --> 00:10:22,120
I'll do whatever you ask.

212
00:10:22,200 --> 00:10:22,679
Wangdui.

213
00:10:23,559 --> 00:10:24,919
A person has to have a conscience.

214
00:10:24,919 --> 00:10:26,120
How could this happen?

215
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:29,559
Why are you all here?

216
00:10:29,679 --> 00:10:30,240
Let's step outside.

217
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:30,879
Step outside.

218
00:10:30,879 --> 00:10:31,879
How could this happen?

219
00:10:31,879 --> 00:10:33,000
Outside, let's talk outside.

220
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:33,720
Let's talk outside.

221
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:36,799
No, Uncle...
